<body>
<p>This site is dedicated to the preprocessing of SOLiD short read sequences. All the perl scripts and the template Excel workbooks here on this page are distributed as open source software under the GPLv3.0. For the Perl Scripts please right click on the link and save the file to the desired location or download the zip file. </p>
<p>A redesigned website is coming soon but the filters and templates are freely available below.</p>
<p><strong><span class="style4">Standard Filter for identification of polyclonal and independant errors for SOLiD short read sequences: </span><br />
</strong>(as discussed in the applications note)<br />
    <br />
  <a href="READ_ME_FILTER.pdf">README Filter (pdf)</a><br /> 
  <a href="SOLiD_preprocess_filter_v2.pl">Preprocessing Filter (SOLiD_preprocess_filter_v2.pl)</a><br />
</p>
<p><strong><span class="style4">Mean Filter</span>:<br />
</strong>Average of the read must exceed the passed QV score (default of 20)<strong>.</strong><br />
  <br />

  <a href="README_Mean_FILTER.pdf">README Mean Filter (pdf) </a><br />
  <a href="SOLiD_preprocess_meanFilter_v2.pl">Mean Filter (SOLiD_preprocess_meanFilter_v2.pl)</a><br /></p>
<p><span class="style4"><strong>SOPRA Filters</strong></span>: <br />
  A <em>de novo </em>assembler for short read sequences developed at Rutgers University. V2 of the filters have been modified so they can also be used with SOPRA<br />
<br />

<p><span class="style4"><strong>Excel Templates for Filter QV Analysis: <br />
</strong></span>These templates will help analyze the QV analysis text file that the filtering script outputs. There is sample data already loaded into the Excel workbooks. <br />
<br />
<a href="README_Excel_template.pdf">README Excel Template (pdf)</a> <br />
<a href="Fragment_QV_analysis.xls">Fragment Template (xls)</a><br />
<a href="mate_pair_QV_analysis.xls">Mate Pair Template (xls)</a><br />
</p>
<p><span class="style4"><strong>QV Assessment of the SOLiD Run: </strong></span><br />
This perl script samples 20% the data (a *_QV.qual file), does several different standard QV analyses on them and outputs a text file. This text file can be placed into the template below to visualize the analysis. This assessment does 9 different analyses on the SOLiD Quality data to get a feel of the quality of the run. This assessment should give a help in decing the parameters desired to run the preprocessing filter. </p>
<p><a href="README_QV_assessment.pdf">README (pdf)</a><br />
<a href="QV_run_assessment.pl">QV_run_assessment.pl</a><br />
<a href="QV_assessment.xls">QV assassment Excel Template (xls) </a> <br /></p>

<p><strong><span class="style4">All of the above mentioned files: </span><br />
</strong>
    <br />
  <a href="SOLiD_preprocess.zip">Preprocessing Files (zip)</a><br />

</p>

